      <description>Standard</description>
    </StandardHierarchyLevel>
    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.7.EE.A.2</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Understand that rewriting an expression in different forms in a problem context can shed light on the problem and how the quantities in it are related. &lt;i&gt;For example, a + 0.05a = 1.05a means that &amp;ldquo;increase by 5%&amp;rdquo; is the same as &amp;ldquo;multiply by 1.05.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/i&gt;</Statement>
    </Statements>
    <GradeLevels>
      <GradeLevel>07</GradeLevel>
    </GradeLevels>
